Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja The Federal Government is set to release an interim report on spendings made by the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19. Auditor-General of the Federation, OAuGF, Anthony Ayine, who disclosed this at an event in Abuja on Wednesday, said the report should be out next week. He said his office had started the audit and was about issuing the first interim report on spendings made on COVID-19. “Hopefully, by next week, the first interim report should be published,” Ayine said. He added, “What we have agreed on is to be issuing quarterly interim reports. “The first interim report coming out would be from the commencement of when the Presidential Task Force for COVID-19 was established up till June 30, 2020.” Copyright PUNCH.
